-- Rogers's Talks to Buy Maple Leaf Sports Stalled Last Summer, Globe Reports
-- B y   D a v i d   S c a n l a n
-- 2010-12-02T03:11:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-02/rogers-s-talks-to-buy-maple-leaf-sports-stalled-globe-link.html
Rogers Communications Inc. was in
talks to buy a majority stake in Maple Leaf Sports &
Entertainment Ltd. this summer though talks with the Ontario
Teachers’ Pension Plan have stalled, the Globe and Mail
reported. The pension fund isn’t actively looking for a buyer of
the company that owns the Toronto Maple Leafs hockey team and
the Raptors basketball club, the paper reported.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scanlan at 
 dscanlan@bloomberg.net  